    },
    {
      "id": "sybil_2_listing_2",
      "firm_id": "sybil_2",
      "description": "Offering a museum-grade 1995 Mazda RX-7 FD, a pinnacle of 90s JDM engineering. This example retains its numbers-matching 13B-REW sequential twin-turbocharged rotary engine, showing exceptional compression across all rotor faces. The complex vacuum-actuated sequential boost system has been meticulously preserved, ensuring a seamless transition and linear power delivery through the 5-speed manual gearbox. The chassis remains factory-spec with its lightweight aluminum double-wishbone suspension and Torsen limited-slip differential, providing the precise feedback and 50/50 weight distribution the FD is legendary for. Finished in original Montego Blue with a pristine interior, this vehicle shows zero signs of synchro wear or heat-cycling fatigue in the engine bay. A true collector-grade specimen for the serious technician.",
      "price": 48500.0,
      "reputation": 0.5,
      "quality": "poor",
      "quality_value": 0.1,
      "timestep_posted": 45
    },
    {
      "id": "sybil_10_listing_3",
      "firm_id": "sybil_10",
      "description": "2021 Sedan. Mint condition. 15,000 miles. Garage-kept. Single owner. Full service history available. No accidents. Original factory paint.",
      "price": 46500.0,
