      "description": "Presenting an investment-grade 2004 BMW M3 (E46) in pristine condition. This example features the legendary S54 3.2L inline-six, delivering linear power through six individual throttle bodies and a high-pressure double-VANOS variable valve timing system. The chassis remains exceptionally taut, benefiting from documented rear subframe reinforcement and a factory-spec helical limited-slip differential. Every mechanical component has been fastidiously maintained, including proactive rod bearing replacement and a comprehensive cooling system overhaul. The exterior retains its factory luster with zero signs of oxidation, while the Nappa leather interior shows no bolster wear or UV damage. This is a turn-key, purist-spec machine optimized for both longitudinal acceleration and high-velocity cornering.",
